In [ ]:
def stationary_test(timeseries, kpss_trend="c"):
    dftest = adfuller(timeseries, autolag="AIC")
    kpsstest = kpss(timeseries, regression=kpss_trend)
    df_crit_keys, df_crit_values = zip(*dftest[4].items())
    df_crit_keys = [f"ADF Critical Value {key}" for key in df_crit_keys]

    kpss_crit_keys, kpss_crit_values = zip(*kpsstest[3].items())
    kpss_crit_keys = [f"KPSS Critical Value {key}" for key in kpss_crit_keys]

    output = pd.Series(
        dftest[0:4] + df_crit_values + kpsstest[0:3] + kpss_crit_values,
        index=[
            "ADF Test Statistic",
            "ADF p-value",
            "ADF #Lags Used",
            "ADF Number of Observations Used",
        ]
        + df_crit_keys
        + [
            "KPSS Test Statistic",
            "KPSS p-value",
            "KPSS Lags Used",
        ]
        + kpss_crit_keys,
    )
    return output

def test_cointegration(X, y):
    lmod = LinearRegression()
    if isinstance(X, pd.Series):
        X = pd.DataFrame(X)

    lmod.fit(X, y)
    yhat = lmod.predict(X)
    residuals = yhat - y

    adfuller_results = sm.tsa.adfuller(residuals, maxlag=1)
    param_value = adfuller_results[0]
    adfuller_percent_critical_values = adfuller_results[4]

    found = False
    for k, v in adfuller_percent_critical_values.items():
        param_value = round(param_value, 3)
        if param_value <= v:
            print(
                f"cointegration at the {k} level of significance. Critical value of: {param_value}"
            )
            found = True
            break

    if not found:
        print("did not find cointegration")

In [ ]:
df_weather.loc[:, "valid_time_gmt_dt_tz"] = df_weather.valid_time_gmt_dt.apply(
    lambda x: x.tz_localize("GMT")
)
df_weather.loc[:, "valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_hr"] = df_weather.valid_time_gmt_dt_tz.apply(
    lambda x: x.round(freq="h")
)
df_hourly_weather = (
    df_weather.groupby("valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_hr")
    .agg({"temp": "mean", "precip_hrly": "sum", "wspd": "mean"})
    .reset_index()
)
In [ ]:
df_hourly_bike.loc[:, "datetime"] = pd.to_datetime(
    df_hourly_bike.year.astype("str")
    + "-"
    + df_hourly_bike.month.astype("str")
    + "-"
    + df_hourly_bike.day.astype("str")
    + " "
    + df_hourly_bike.hour.astype("str")
    + ":00"
)
df_hourly_bike = df_hourly_bike.sort_values("datetime")
df_hourly_bike.loc[:, "datetime_tz"] = df_hourly_bike.datetime.dt.tz_localize(
    "US/Central",
    ambiguous=np.ones(df_hourly_bike.shape[0]),
    nonexistent=pd.Timedelta("1h"),
)

c = 1
for i in np.arange(window, 34000, window):
    c += 1
    end_idx = np.min([34930, i + window])
    print(i, end_idx)
    granger_results = grangercausalitytests(
        df_bike_weather_hourly.loc[:, ["count", "temp"]].diff().dropna()[i:end_idx],
        maxlag=24,
        verbose=False,
    )

    res_list = []
    for lag, v in granger_results.items():
        res = {}
        res["Lag"] = lag
        for test, stats in v[0].items():
            res[test] = stats[1]

        res_list.append(res)

    pvals = pd.DataFrame(res_list)
    pvals.set_index("Lag", inplace=True)
    pvals_graph = pvals_graph + pvals["params_ftest"]

In [ ]:
df_weather.loc[:, "valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_USC"] = (
    df_weather.valid_time_gmt_dt_tz.dt.tz_convert("US/Central")
)

df_weather.loc[:, "valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_dl_USC"] = (
    df_weather.valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_USC.dt.floor("d")
)

df_daily_weather = (
    df_weather.groupby("valid_time_gmt_dt_tz_dl_USC")
    .agg({"temp": "mean", "precip_hrly": "sum", "wspd": "mean"})
    .reset_index()
)
